20/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Justice Minister Aldo Bumci is urging domestic mobile phone operators -- AMC and Vodafone -- to provide extra security measures in support of the government's fight against organised crime and terrorism. Bumci, who attended Monday's (19 September) inauguration ceremony for the Court of Serious Crimes in Tirana, is asking the two wireless carriers to register all subscribers and users of their services, tape conversations and keep a database. 
In other news Monday, the Inspectorate for Assets Control announced that all members of the new government and parliament should submit their wealth and annual income declarations by 3 October. Inspectorate chief Fatmira Laskaj said this requirement should prevent conflicts of interest, particularly in regards to the ministers. (Albanian News - 20/09/05)
